contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|pct}} '''PCT''' can mean: == Geography == * [[Pacific Crest Trail]], a hiking trail that runs along the west coast of the United States, from Mexico to Canada * [[Princeton Airport (New Jersey)]] (IATA: PCT) == History == * [[Paleolithic Continuity Theory]] == Law == * [[Patent Cooperation Treaty]], an international patent treaty == Medicine == * Patient Care Technician, a type of [[Unlicensed assistive personnel]] * [[Porphyria cutanea tarda]], a form of [[porphyria]] * [[Postcoital test]], a test for [[infertility]] * [[Post-coital tristesse]] * [[Primary Care Trust]], a form of administrive body in the United Kingdom National Health service, replaced in 2013 by clinical commissioning groups * [[Procalcitonin]], a precursor of the hormone [[calcitonin]] * [[Proximal convoluted tubule]], a part of the [[nephron]] of the kidney == Science and technology == * pct, abbreviation for [[percent]] * [[Perceptual control theory]], a theory of purposeful behavior in all living things * [[Polychlorinated terphenyl]], an industrial chemical and environmental contaminant * [[Polycyclohexylenedimethylene terephthalate]], a thermoplastic polyester * [[Private Communications Technology]], an obsolete Internet security protocol * [[Programmable Communicating Thermostat]] == Society, culture and sports == * ''[[Communist Party of Togo|Parti Communiste du Togo]]'' (in French) * ''[[Tunisian Communist Party|Parti Communiste Tunisien]]'' (in French) * ''[[Parti Congolais du Travail]]'' (in French) * [[P.C.T]], Hip-Hop musicians * Post-cycle therapy, class of drugs and administration regime employed to restore a user's natural hormone production after [[ergogenic use of anabolic steroids]] * [[NHS Primary Care Trust]], part of the United Kingdom's National Health Service * [[Presbyterian Church in Taiwan]] * Production Car Trial - see [[Classic Trials]] {{disambig}}
